      <title>Not that Kind of Hot Dog</title>
      <link>https://ryanstraight.com/2018/07/24/not-that-kind-of-hot-dog/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 24 Jul 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://ryanstraight.com/2018/07/24/not-that-kind-of-hot-dog/</guid>
      <description>

&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s hot outside in Arizona. I mean, it&amp;rsquo;s hot virtually everywhere, to be fair. We&amp;rsquo;re at the very beginning of an extreme heat advisory that lasts from yesterday (July 23, 2018) morning all the way through Wednesday night. It&amp;rsquo;s dangerously hot.&lt;sup class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; id=&#34;fnref:1&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:1&#34;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; Keep in mind it&amp;rsquo;s actually hotter &lt;em&gt;today&lt;/em&gt; than it was yesterday. Today it&amp;rsquo;s a high of 112F (44.4C). The images you&amp;rsquo;ll find below were taken on a day with a high of 109F (42.7C).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now, you know about our dogs and how much we love them. (Read: spoil.) Considering the excessive heat warning, I began wondering just how hot the back yard gets during the day. I know the general numbers but what about in our actual back yard where our actual dogs actually walk around, actually?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I wanted to demonstrate what I talked about back in my Thermoception episode of The New Professor&lt;sup class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; id=&#34;fnref:2&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:2&#34;&gt;2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;: the difference between ambient air temperature and the temperature of the pavement. This is especially important for animals.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Recently having procured an infrared thermometer to use when cooking, it occurred to me I could use it to really illustrate these dangers. These are taken in the same spots throughout the day. You&amp;rsquo;ll see when and how the shade from the house alters the temperature. Please, think about this when you want to take your dogs out.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While it&amp;rsquo;s not a perfect analog, consider these water temperatures and time required for &amp;ldquo;deep burn.&amp;rdquo;&lt;sup class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; id=&#34;fnref:3&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:3&#34;&gt;3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

